    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I moved this out of 0.13. \r\n\r\nAs I explain in the comment on the PR I had created (https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/pull/10961#issuecomment-1589708743), this issue cannot be solved by using `requestContactInfo`, because the root cause is that the contacts haven't been online for more than 9 days.\r\n\r\nWithout my changes, I was able to get the right display name by logging in and forcing a contact update, then the account seeing the 3 word name updated from the mailserver.\r\n\r\nSo we can't actually fix this problem 100%. We cannot ensure that the contact info of someone will be propagated in the last 9 days.It's the same for https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/8022.\r\n\r\nWe could use new designs to just show something else than the 3 word name, but it still wouldn't be the display name.\r\nOtherwise, we could increase the mailsever fetch range, but the issue still happens for accounts older than the new cut off date.",
